                                    It incorporates fields such as the study of Japanese language, culture, history, literature,
                                    art, music, and science. Its roots may be traced back to the Dutch at Dejima, Nagasaki in the
                                    Edo period. The foundation of the Asiatic Society of Japan at Yokohama in 1872 by men such as
                                    Ernest Satow and Frederick Victor Dickins was an important event in the development of Japanese
